Manchester United maintained its
seven-point lead in English soccerâ€™s Premier League with a 2-1
win against Liverpool, as second-place Manchester City defeated
10-man Arsenal 2-0.  Robin van Persie  and Nemanja Vidic got the goals for United
at its Old Trafford stadium, with halftime substitute Daniel
Sturridge replying for Liverpool.   Arsenal played more than 80 minutes with 10 men after
Laurent Koscielny was red-carded for bringing down Edin Dzeko in
the penalty area. James Milner and Dzeko scored for City, which
had defender  Vincent Kompany  dismissed after 75 minutes.  United has 55 points, City is on 48, with Chelsea another
seven points back. Tottenham has 40 points. Arsenal remains in
sixth and Liverpool eighth.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
